com.yworks.yfiles.graphml

Class AbstractInputHandler<TKey,TData>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.graphml.AbstractInputHandler<TKey,TData>
  • Type Parameters:
    TKey - The type of the key, i.e. the items that are associated with the data in the GraphML.
    TData - The type of the data that is associated with the keys.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IInputHandler
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MapperInputHandler

    public abstract class AbstractInputHandler<TKey,TData>
extends Object
implements IInputHandler
    An abstract convenience implementation of the IInputHandler interface.

    • Method Detail

      • applyDefault

        public void applyDefault(IParseContext context)
        This method is invoked when no data tag is defined, and the default value should be applied.

        This implementation delegates to setValue(IParseContext, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object) if a default exists using the DefaultValue.

        Specified by:
        applyDefault in interface IInputHandler
        Parameters:
        context - the current parse context.

      • getDefaultValue

        public final TData getDefaultValue()
        Gets the default value that will be applied to the keys where the data attribute is missing.

        If any default value is set (including null), DefaultExisting is automatically set to true.

        Returns:
        The default value.
        See Also:
        setDefaultValue(java.lang.Object)

      • initializeFromKeyDefinition

        public void initializeFromKeyDefinition(IParseContext context,
                                        Element definition)
                                 throws IOException
        Initializes this instance from the GraphML key definition.

        This implementation looks for the GraphML default element and delegates to parseDataCore(IParseContext, Node) if a default is found to store the DefaultValue.

        Throws:
        IOException
        Parameters:
        context - The context.
        definition - The definition.

      • isDefaultExisting

        public final boolean isDefaultExisting()
        Gets a value indicating whether a default value has been set, either through a key definition element or explicitly by assigning a value to the DefaultValue property.

        If this property is set to true, the applyDefault(IParseContext) method will call the setValue(IParseContext, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object) method using the DefaultValue as the value parameter.

        Returns:
        true if the default value exists; false otherwise.

      • isDefaultValueParsingEnabled

        public final boolean isDefaultValueParsingEnabled()
        Gets a value indicating whether the default value in the key definition should be parsed.
        Returns:
        true if the default value should be parsed; false otherwise. The default is true.
        See Also:
        setDefaultValueParsingEnabled(boolean)

      • parseData

        public void parseData(IParseContext context,
                      Node node)
               throws IOException
        This method is invoked each time a data element with matching key is processed.

        If the current element is of the same type as this TKey, this method delegates the actual parsing to parseDataCore(IParseContext, Node) and setValue(IParseContext, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object)

        Specified by:
        parseData in interface IInputHandler
        Throws:
        IOException - If the data cannot be written
        Parameters:
        context - the current parse context.
        node - the DOM node representing the data element.
